responses.content:
```yaml
leads:
  - headline: Prototype Pollution in qs.parse
    analysis: |
      The `parseKeys` function in `lib/parse.js` is vulnerable to prototype pollution. If an attacker can control the keys of the parsed object, they can set properties on `Object.prototype` by using keys like `__proto__[polluted]` in the query string.

      For example, parsing the query string `__proto__[polluted]=test` would result in `Object.prototype.polluted` being set to `test`. This could allow an attacker to modify the behavior of the application or execute arbitrary code.
    cwe: CWE-1321
    function_names:
      - parseKeys
    filenames:
      - lib/parse.js
    classification: very promising
```

leads.headline: Prototype Pollution in qs.parse
leads.analysis:
The parseKeys function in lib/parse.js is vulnerable to prototype pollution. If an attacker can control the keys of the parsed object, they can set properties on Object.prototype by using keys like __proto__[polluted] in the query string.

For example, parsing the query string __proto__[polluted]=test would result in Object.prototype.polluted being set to test. This could allow an attacker to modify the behavior of the application or execute arbitrary code.
